Razgulay May Sell Assets to United Grain, Razgulay Director Says

-- B y   M a r i n a   S y s o y e v a
-- 
2011-04-13T07:28:58Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-13/razgulay-may-sell-assets-to-united-grain-razgulay-director-says.html
Razgulay Group (GRAZ) , a Russian sugar and
rice producer, is in talks to sell some assets to United Grain
Co.,  Russia ’s state-owned grain trader, according to Razgulay
board member Dmitry Shteinsapir.  The assets that may change hands include some of Razgulay’s
grain elevators, Shteinsapir said at a company presentation in
Moscow yesterday. United Grain spokesman Viktor Krupenin
confirmed the talks. Razgulay wants to focus on its rice and
sugar production, and purchases of land within 200 kilometers
(124 miles) of its sugar plants, he said. Razgulay has 10 sugar
plants, company spokeswoman Ekaterina Agibalova said.  To contact the reporter on this story: Marina Sysoyeva in Moscow
   msysoyeva@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story: Claudia
Carpenter at   ccarpenter2@bloomberg.net  